  "body": "*Issue:*\r\nCurrently when importing from `_colors.py` there is a try except wrapped around the matplotlib import.\r\nIn the except clause there is only a `pass` command which means if the matplotlib import fails there is no hint for the failing matplotlib import but instead an import error for the colors:\r\n\r\nImportError: cannot import name 'red_blue' from 'shap.plots.colors._colors'\r\n\r\n*Solution:*\r\nRemove the try except wrapper around the `from matplotlib.colors import LinearSegmentedColormap` and remove the `import matplotlib` completely. This means the correct import error is thrown and is not hidden anymore by the pass command.\r\n\r\n```python\r\n\"\"\" This defines some common colors.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nfrom __future__ import division\r\n\r\nimport numpy as np\r\nfrom ._colorconv import lab2rgb, lch2lab\r\n\r\nfrom matplotlib.colors import LinearSegmentedColormap\r\n...\r\n```",
